      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ac09931e0b42b33a",
      "text": "Only writing and printing suggest the connection of communication processes that do not react to the unity of communication and information, but precisely to their difference: Processes of truth control, processes of articulating a suspicion with subsequent universalization of the suspicion in a psychoanalytical and/or ideological direction."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3d0b76f43ea01ff4",
      "text": "Writing and printing thus enforce the experience of difference that constitutes communication: they are, in this precise sense, more communicative forms of communication, and they thus induce reaction of communication to communication in a much more specific sense than is possible in the form of oral exchange (Wechselrede)."
    },
